screen_desc: The screenshot displays a settings menu for language options in a messaging app. At the top, there is a section titled "Translate Messages" with options to show a translate button and to translate entire chats. Below this, there is a note indicating that the 'Translate' button will appear when tapping on a text message and that Google may have access to the translated text. The language selection list shows "English" as the selected option, followed by other languages including Arabic, Belarusian, Catalan, Croatian, Czech, and Dutch.
